Package jdrasil.algorithms.postprocessing

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FlattenTreeDecomposition<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    A tree-decomposition may contain useless bags.
    ImproveTreeDecomposition<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    This postprocessor allows to improve the quality of the decomposition (whenever we know that we do not have an optimal decomposition) with the separator technique of "Treewidth computations I.
    NiceTreeDecomposition<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    A \emph{nice} tree decomposition is a \emph{rooted} tree decomposition in which each bag has one of the following types: \begin{enumerate} \item A \emph{leaf} bag has no children and stores and empty set.
    Postprocessor<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    A Postprocessor is a function that maps a given arbitrary tree decomposition to another tree decomposition of the same graph.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    NiceTreeDecomposition.BagType
    Every bag in a nice tree decomposition has a specific type (leaf, join, introduce, forget, edge).
